The paper is about a method for combining results of isolated ranker models in retrieval tasks, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The method proposed in the paper is based on graph theory and machine learning techniques, which are also relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely to be relevant to the paper.
